<p class="heading"><a name="4">Member Guidelines</a> <a class="top" href="#top">[TOP]</a></p>
 <p>See "Guild Tag", "Raid Attendance", and "Removal".</p>
  <p class="heading"><a name="4a">Guild Tag</a> <a class="top" href="#top">[TOP]</a></p>
   
   <p>When you plan to de-guilding yourself, talk to an officer first. Do not play around with your guild tag. If you do de-guild, you will have to reapply 
   should you change your mind. Do not let people outside of the guild play your characters with the guild tag unless directly supervised. If you are not 
   absolutely certain, please guildremove yourself before letting your friends play your character.</p>
   
   <p class="heading"><a name="4b">Raid Attendance</a> <a class="top" href="#top">[TOP]</a></p>
   <p>The purpose of all of this work is to try and make things fair to everyone in Fury's Edge. Whether you are EST/PST/Overseas, play 40 hours a week, 
   play 10 hours a week, etc, we want everyone to be dedicated to pushing the guild further in what we do.<p>

   <p>We also want to see people rewarded based on there dedication / attitude to the guild. The people that put in the extra effort or at least the best 
   effort they can should be the people that benefit.<p>

   <p>Attendance points are going to be tracked by the officers and posted publicly. These points will also be used for loot distriibution.</p>
   
   <p class="heading"><a name="4c">Removal</a> <a class="top" href="#top">[TOP]</a></p>
   <p>When you plan to de-guilding yourself, talk to an officer first. Do not play around with your guild tag. If you do de-guild, you will have to reapply 
   should you change your mind. Do not let people outside of the guild play your characters with the guild tag unless directly supervised. If you are not 
   absolutely certain, please guildremove yourself before letting your friends play your character.</p>

<p class="heading"><a name="5">Alternate Characters</a> <a class="top" href="#top">[TOP]</a></p>
 <p>Alts are by no means meant to take priority over a Main Character. A few restrictive measures are in place to ensure this:</p>
  <ul>
   <li>1 guilded Alt per member.</li>
   <li>Point pool is based off of the main character only.</li>
   <li>New members must be guilded for 3 months prior to adding an Alt.</li>
  </ul>
